# Comma-separated camera nodes: id|name|host  (host = bare host or IP).
# Prefer .local hostnames so DHCP IP changes don't break the panel — needs
# working IPv4 mDNS on the laptop (avahi-daemon running + `mdns4_minimal
# [NOTFOUND=return]` in /etc/nsswitch.conf's hosts line). Both the server-side
# calls and the browser <img> streams then track each Pi's current IP. Fall back
# to raw IPs if mDNS isn't set up.
SMARTROOM_NODES=cam1|Smartroom 1|smartroom1.local,cam2|Smartroom 2|smartroom2.local

# Port the panel listens on.
PORT=4000

# Where "Save All to Laptop" writes recordings (default: ./recordings/ in the
# project, which is gitignored). Override to an absolute path if you want.
# SMARTROOM_SAVE_DIR=/home/alawn/Code/smartroom-control/recordings

# Person-detection (detect/detect.py + /api/detect). Defaults reuse the
# yolo-bench venv + pre-exported OpenVINO models. Each model in SMARTROOM_YOLO_MODELS
# must have <key>_openvino_model/ under SMARTROOM_YOLO_DIR; the dashboard toggles
# between them (nano / small / medium).
# SMARTROOM_DETECT_PYTHON=/home/alawn/Code/yolo-bench/.venv/bin/python
# SMARTROOM_YOLO_MODELS=yolo26n,yolo26s,yolo26m,yolo26l,yolo26n-pose
# (a model key containing "pose" runs the pose task: draws skeletons and also
#  writes camera_main.keypoints.<model>.json for downstream action recognition)
# SMARTROOM_YOLO_DIR=/home/alawn/Code/yolo-bench
# SMARTROOM_DETECT_IMGSZ=640
# SMARTROOM_DETECT_SAMPLE_FPS=5
# SMARTROOM_DETECT_ANNOTATE=1   # set 0 for JSON-only (skip annotated video)
